arâ€”this isnâ€™t financial advice. Think of it as education. My goal is to give you clarity, confidence, and a roadmap.\n\nAt the end of our session, youâ€™ll get three things: a PDF Report, a Summary, and a Full Transcript. These are yours to keep. You can use them on your ownâ€”or, even better, take them to a qualified financial advisor.\n\nHereâ€™s a simple way to think about it. If you have a small fever, you can probably treat yourself. But for something more serious, youâ€™d see a doctorâ€”ideally with a clear brief of whatâ€™s going on. This conversation gives you that briefâ€¦ so you can make the very best use of an advisorâ€™s time.\n\nSoâ€”if youâ€™re ready to begin, our first topic is: â€œWhy learn about financial anxiety now?â€\nWhen you are, just say: Dive in.','\n',char(10)));
